  "commentary": "With SPX at 6812.47 sitting between the GEX flip at 6800 and the massive +66.6B gamma wall at 6830, dealers are currently in hedging mode as long gamma holders, providing stabilizing flows by selling into any move toward 6830 and buying dips toward 6800. The thick positive gamma zone from 6810-6840 creates strong resistance overhead, while the PIN regime suggests mean reversion dynamics will dominate with dealers acting as natural counterparties to momentum. Key levels to watch are the 6800 flip strike as support and the 6830 max gamma strike as resistance, with dealer selling pressure intensifying on any push toward the 6820-6830 zone.\n\nBottom line: expect the market to trade in a tight range between 6800-6830 with dealers capping moves higher.",
